data.col_1: Expected transit times are provided for standard service level
Deferred service level has typically 3 days longer transit than standard service level
Expedite service level has typically 1-3 days shorter transit than standard service level
Volume (kg) shared is the average per qtr volume (Q1 2023 to Q3 2024)
Profile showing approximate percentage of volume during a quarter:
1st 10 weeks of the qtr - 40% of average qtrly volume
Last 3 weeks of the qtr - 60% of average qtrly volume

Outbound Singapore volume is based on projections as there is no historical data. 
Singapore distribution hub soft launch is in Oct 24, so we do not have a full qtr of actual shipment volume to share
Typically shipment not more than 6 pallets per AWB, min 1 carton.

Outbound China (Suzhou) volume to all lanes (except Suzhou-Singapore) is based on historical data.
AMD expects a 20-40% progressive reduction in volume for these lanes as the volume would be diverted to Singapore for order fulfilment
Suzhou - Singapore volume is based on projection of inventory transfers from Suzhou to Singapore hub, to turn around for order fulfilment from Singapore hub to end customers

Outbound Malaysia (Penang) volume to all lanes is based on historical data.
AMD expects a 20-30% progressive reduction in volume for these lanes as the volume would be diverted to Singapore for order fulfilment

Most palletized shipments use 1000X1200mm pallets, maximum height 1600mm
Intra-Europe shipments use 800X1200mm EUR pallets
HKG PCP Partner shipments may use 1100X1100mm or 760X760mm pallets
